# cspell:word atas
# Solana mainnet RPC + WS endpoints.
#
# Optional — the app ships with free public defaults that allow browser
# traffic and apply rate limits per end-user IP. For a beta-sized app the
# defaults are usually fine. Override here if you want a different provider
# (higher limits, lower latency, private endpoint).
#
# Security note — these are NEXT_PUBLIC_* variables, so values ship in the
# browser bundle and are visible to anyone who opens devtools. If you set a
# keyed provider URL, treat the key as a public identifier, not a secret:
#
#   1. Use separate keys per environment so a leak in one is contained.
#
#      Local dev:  restrict by source IP (your home/office IP).
#                  This is real protection — IPs can't be forged from a browser.
#      Production: restrict by allowed origin/domain (your prod + preview hosts).
#                  This blocks "another site embedding your key in user
#                  browsers"; it does not stop server-side abuse from a leaked
#                  key. Treat the quota ceiling as the blast radius and rotate
#                  on suspicion.
#
#   2. For full exfiltration resistance, proxy RPC requests through your own
#      server so the key never enters the bundle. Worth doing once cost or
#      abuse becomes a real concern.
NEXT_PUBLIC_RPC_URL=
NEXT_PUBLIC_WS_URL=

# DFlow platform fee.
#
# When set, the swap path adds `platformFeeBps` + `feeAccount` to every
# /order request, and DFlow forwards the fee to the matching ATA after the
# trade lands. Fee is collected from the OUTPUT token (DFlow's default
# `platformFeeMode=outputMint`), so one ATA per output mint is required.
#
# Setup — before enabling, the fee wallet must already own an ATA for every
# mint in lib/currencies.json. Run `pnpm setup-fee-atas` once (and again after
# adding new currencies) to create them. The DFlow API rejects /order if the
# feeAccount doesn't already exist, and even an *uncollected* fee declaration
# eats into slippage tolerance — so leave BPS empty to disable the fee, never
# leave it set while the wallet has missing ATAs.
#
# BPS — basis points. 1 bps = 0.01%. 50 = 0.5%, 100 = 1%. Empty/unset = no fee.
#
# WALLET — base58 pubkey of the wallet that owns the fee ATAs. The per-trade
# feeAccount is derived at request time from this owner + the trade's output
# mint, matching the token program (classic vs Token-2022) recorded in
# currencies.json. The pubkey is a destination address, so NEXT_PUBLIC_ is
# fine — never put the secret key here.
NEXT_PUBLIC_PLATFORM_FEE_BPS=
NEXT_PUBLIC_PLATFORM_FEE_WALLET=
